javadoc:
Interface for sets of graph objects which have keys such as vertices
 and edges.

The modification number is a counter for the number of changes

methods.javadoc: Returns the number of KeyedObjects in this KeyIndexableSet
methods.name: size
methods.comment: Returns the number of KeyedObjects in this KeyIndexableSet

methods.javadoc:
Returns the number of KeyedObjects this KeyIndexableSet can
 hold without growing.
methods.name: capacity
methods.comment:
Returns the number of KeyedObjects this KeyIndexableSet can
 hold without growing.

methods.javadoc:
Adds a KeyedObject to this KeyIndexableSet. The set will increase
 in capacity if needed.
@return true if the KeyedObject was successfully added. Returns false
 if the KeyedObject is null or already in the KeyIndexableSet or addition
 fails for some other reason.
methods.name: add
methods.comment:
Adds a KeyedObject to this KeyIndexableSet. The set will increase
 in capacity if needed.

return.comment:
true if the KeyedObject was successfully added. Returns false
 if the KeyedObject is null or already in the KeyIndexableSet or addition
 fails for some other reason.

methods.name: remove
methods.comment: Remove a KeyedObject from this KeyIndexableSet.

return.comment:
true if the KeyedObject was sucessfully removed. Returns false
 if the KeyedObject was not in the KeyIndexablrSet.

methods.javadoc: Returns true if this KeyIndexableSet contains the specified KeyedObject.
methods.name: contains
methods.comment: Returns true if this KeyIndexableSet contains the specified KeyedObject.

 hasNext()/next() style. See GraphIterator.
methods.name: iterator
methods.comment:

methods.javadoc:

 KeyedObjects.

methods.comment:
Returns the elements of this KeyIndexableSet as an array of

methods.javadoc:
Returns the KeyedObject with the specified key in this KeyIndexableSet.
 Returns null if the Set contains no object with that key.
methods.name: getKeyedObject
methods.comment:
Returns the KeyedObject with the specified key in this KeyIndexableSet.
 Returns null if the Set contains no object with that key.
